Ext.data.JsonP['Problems_with_WST_and_PDT']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>Problems with WST and PDT</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-30083814\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>Problems with WST and PDT</h1>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083814_ProblemswithWSTandPDT-Contents\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Contents</span></h2>\n<ul class=\"toc-indentation \"><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Problems_with_WST_and_PDT-section-src-30083814_ProblemswithWSTandPDT-ProblemDescription\">Problem Description</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Problems_with_WST_and_PDT-section-src-30083814_ProblemswithWSTandPDT-ProblemSource\">Problem Source</a>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p><a class=\"document-link \" href=\"#!/guide/Problems_with_WST_and_PDT-section-src-30083814_ProblemswithWSTandPDT-SuggestedWorkaround\">Suggested Workaround</a>    </p>\n</li></ul>    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083814_ProblemswithWSTandPDT-ProblemDescription\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Problem Description</span></h2>\n    <p>In some cases, when installing WST/PDT side-by-side with the Studio, scripts cannot be opened correctly with the WST/PDT editors that were assigned to work on the same file extensions that the Studio is assigned to.<br>A reported error of <i class=\" \">&quot;Unsupported content type in editor&quot;</i> is opened, and the edited content is displayed as simple text.    </br></p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083814_ProblemswithWSTandPDT-ProblemSource\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Problem Source</span></h2>\n    <p>This problem is originated in a known WST issue that can be viewed at <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=268635\" target=\"_blank\">https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=268635</a>. The issue&apos;s affect on the Studio is explained in details at <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"https://jira.appcelerator.org/browse/APSTUD-3185\" target=\"_blank\">https://jira.appcelerator.org/browse/APSTUD-3185</a>.    </p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-30083814_ProblemswithWSTandPDT-SuggestedWorkaround\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Suggested Workaround</span></h2>\n    <p>To be able to open those files with the WST/PDT editors, you will need to remove the <i class=\" \">Aptana Natures</i> from your project.    </p>\n<ol class=\" \"><li class=\" \">    <p>Right click the project and select <i class=\" \">Properties</i>    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Select the <i class=\" \">Project Natures</i> item    </p>\n</li><li class=\" \">    <p>Uncheck the <i class=\" \">Aptana Natures</i> (PHP &amp; Web)    </p>\n</li></ol>    <p>This workaround will allow you opening the files. However, the <i class=\" \">Nature</i> change will have an effect on the features that Studio can provide while working with that specific project (Code Assist, Debugging, etc.).    </p>\n    </div>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=30083814\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"Problems with WST and PDT"});